-- MOVES-Stefan Pfister head of KPMG Switzerland
-- 
-- Fri Aug 29, 2014 08:30AM EDT
-- None



Aug 29 (Reuters) - KMPG LLP, a global network of professional firms providing audit, tax and advisory services, named Stefan Pfister the new chief executive officer in Switzerland, effective from Oct. 1.

Pfister, previously the head of advisory of KPMG in Switzerland, replaces Roger Neininger, who was elected as chairperson of the board of directors. Helene Beguin and Stuart Robertson were elected as members of the board.